Patricia Q. Stonesifer /ˈstoʊnsaɪfər/ (born 1956) is the President and CEO of Martha's Table, a non-profit in Washington, D.C., that develops sustainable solutions to poverty.[1][2] Stonesifer currently advises business, nonprofit and government leaders on strategies for reducing inequity, and was appointed in 2010 by President Obama to serve as the Chair of the White House Council for Community Solutions.[3] In July 1996, she was named as one of the 25 Most Influential People in America by Time.[4]



