P.L. 107-101, S.J. Res. 26
S.J. Res. 8 (2007)


Notes:
Newsmakers. The people behind today's headlines. 1997 Cumulation. Detroit: Gale Research, 1998; Who's Who of American Women. 20th edition, 1997-1998. New Providence, NJ: Marquis Who's Who, 1996.


Summary:
Committees/Roles: Chair, Board of Regents, 9/2008-1/2012; Vice-Chair, 1/2012-1/2013. This is a newly created role, in response to governance issues during the previous seven years. Chair, Nominating Committee; Audit and Review Committee; ad hoc Committee on Facilities Renovation; ad hoc Committee on Board of Regents Governance
Occupation: Foundation executive
Number of Terms: 2
Biography: Patricia Q. (Patty) Stonesifer of Washington was the chief executive officer of the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation, the nation's largest philanthropic organization from January 2006 to January 2008. She previously worked at Microsoft Corp. from 1988-1997, including serving as senior vice president, where she launched its cable TV and Internet news ventures, MSNBC and MSN. Ms. Stonesifer has served as a member of the U.S. delegation to the United Nations General Assembly Special Session on HIV/AIDS and currently is on the boards of DATA (Debt, AIDS, Trade, Africa), Amazon.com, and The Seattle Foundation.


Contact information:
Institutional History Division, Smithsonian Institution Archives, 600 Maryland Avenue, S.W., Washington, D.C. 20024-2520, SIHistory@si.edu


